The paper discusses Markov Brains, which are a type of artificial neural network that can be evolved through optimization. This falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning, which is covered by cs.NE. Additionally, the paper discusses techniques for studying and evolving Markov Brains, which are relevant to the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The Markov Brains are also used to control motor outputs, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY) and robotics (cs.RO).
